@NODE 4.1. "Gadgets"

Gadgets

Here you can set some presets:

Hide-Button:
- iconifies the Window

Closegadget or QUIT:
- exits the program.

Info:
- shows the version of ScriptFile.

Output | "«":
- sets the outputpath. « will call the Requester.

Requester:
- The program will request the outputpath of the scripted file.

Start window:
- start program as AppWindow or AppIcon 
  (ATTENTION: prefs will be written after clicking this gadget)


@ENDNODE

@NODE 4.3. "Prefs"

The Prefs-Option has been deleted


@ENDNODE
@NODE 4.9 "WBSTART © STEFAN BECKER"

WBSTART © STEFAN BECKER

WBStart by Stefan Becker has following features:
- Programs behave like started on their original device (tooltypes included)
- Project-Icons are identified!
- Texts are shown by their default tool.

You should use WBStart V>=1.4.
WBStart can be found in Aminet (or on Aminet-CD) in util/cli/ .

Special thanx to Stefan Becker!

Create two files named exe and text in s:sf/ with any text-editor.
type in:

c:wbstarter %s

and save it.


@ENDNODE 
@NODE 5. "Installation"

Installation


Click the installer-Icon and something wonderful will happen!




If nothing happens, you must copy some files:

File                         Destination dir

Scriptfile & ~.info          Whereeveryouwant
Scriptfile.guide & ~.info    Whereeveryouwant
Def:sf.info                  Sys:prefs/Env-Archive/ 

New in 3.0:
You have to create the dir s:sf


That's all.


@ENDNODE

